{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-modules-jsx","path":"/modules/rails","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><a href=\"http://jenkins.terasology.org/view/Modules/job/Rails/\"><img src=\"http://jenkins.terasology.org/view/Modules/job/Rails/badge/icon\" alt=\"Build Status\"></a></p>\n<h1 id=\"rails\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#rails\" aria-label=\"rails permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Rails</h1>\n<p><strong>Rails</strong> is a Terasology module that adds rail transport into the game. It helps the player to travel far distances faster and easier than ever before.</p>\n<h1 id=\"items\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#items\" aria-label=\"items permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Items</h1>\n<h2 id=\"rails-1\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#rails-1\" aria-label=\"rails 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Rails</h2>\n<p>Rails are the most fundamental part of this module. They are the tracks on which carts can travel.</p>\n<h2 id=\"carts\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#carts\" aria-label=\"carts permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Carts</h2>\n<p>A cart is a vehicle that can travel on rails. This module contains a simplistic cart which can be ridden by the player. It moves only when pushed by the player or dragged by a connected cart.</p>\n<h2 id=\"wrench\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#wrench\" aria-label=\"wrench permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Wrench</h2>\n<p>The wrench is a tool that can be used to perform specific actions like connecting carts with each other or changing the direction of a tee joint.</p>\n<p>For additional items like locomotives and special rails to use with <strong>Rails</strong>, please take a look at the <a href=\"https://github.com/Terasology/AdditionalRails\">AdditionalRails</a> module.</p>\n<h1 id=\"getting-started\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#getting-started\" aria-label=\"getting started permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Getting Started</h1>\n<ol>\n<li>Create a new world with the Rails module enabled</li>\n<li>You should see a wrench and a cart item in your inventory.</li>\n<li>Press <kbd>F1</kbd> to open up the console and type in <code class=\"language-text\">give rails:rails</code> to obtain rail blocks, which will be available in the inventory. Repeat this step when you need more rail blocks.</li>\n<li>Place rail blocks on top of other blocks to build a track.</li>\n<li>To place a cart on a track, select the cart item in your inventory and place it (right-click) on a rail block as you would place a normal block. The cart will automatically align itself with the track.</li>\n</ol>\n<h1 id=\"creating-tracks\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#creating-tracks\" aria-label=\"creating tracks permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Creating Tracks</h1>\n<p>Tracks are built by placing rail blocks. When a rail block is placed, it automatically connects to nearby rail blocks to form contiguous track segments. Rail blocks can be straight or sloped and can form a corner, T (tee) junction, or an intersection.</p>\n<h1 id=\"connecting-carts\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#connecting-carts\" aria-label=\"connecting carts permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Connecting Carts</h1>\n<p>You can connect two carts as follows:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Place two carts on two adjacent rail blocks such that they are very close to each other.</li>\n<li>Select the wrench in your inventory and right-click on a cart</li>\n<li>You now have a connection between the two carts. On pushing one cart, the other cart should follow suit.</li>\n</ol>\n<h1 id=\"testing\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#testing\" aria-label=\"testing permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Testing</h1>\n<p>You can verify whether or not all of the functionality in <strong>Rails</strong> is working perfectly by following the <a href=\"https://github.com/Terasology/Rails/wiki/Rails-Test-Plan\">Test Plan</a> that has been written in the repository's wiki.</p>","timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"Build Status Rails Rails is a Terasology module that adds rail transport into the game. It helps the player to travel far distances fasterâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"Rails","cover":{"publicURL":"/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/cover.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#f8f8f8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/9e1f0/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/8dfb2/cover.jpg 480w,\n/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/2f986/cover.jpg 960w,\n/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/9e1f0/cover.jpg 1920w","sizes":"(min-width: 1920px) 1920px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/3fa69/cover.webp 480w,\n/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/986c9/cover.webp 960w,\n/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/34dc0/cover.webp 1920w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 1920px) 1920px, 100vw"}]},"width":1920,"height":1000}}},"date":null,"tags":["Library","Asset"]},"fields":{"slug":"/rails","date":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/rails"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1865044719"]}